In March, the House overwhelmingly passed the Pandemic Unemployment Fraud Enforcement Act to extend the statute of limitations to prosecute criminals who stole billions in COVID-era unemployment insurance benefits.

@USDOL Inspector General’s Office has ID'd a number of investigations involving millions of tax dollars that have been or will be jeopardized in the future if the Senate fails to act on this bill.

Every day the Senate delays is another day criminals are getting away with the greatest theft of tax dollars in U.S. history.

President Trump is correct. We cannot allow our universities to become incubation chambers for antisemitism and extremism.

@WaysandMeansGOP's investigation last Congress revealed several tax exempt universities had utterly failed -- in some cases willfully -- to protect their Jewish students.

We must continue to hold bad actors accountable.

For years, bureaucrats have unlawfully tried to control Washington without the consent of Congress.

The Biden Administration has spent $1 TRILLION with the stroke of a pen.

@ElonMusk and @VivekGRamaswamy will stop the bureaucratic state that is outrageously indebting Americans.
